2. Format timestamps as ISO strings
3. Include file existence check (warn if deleted)
4. Sort by timestamp descending (newest first)

Check status of a running video generation operation.

Parameters:
- operationId: string (required) - Operation ID from pending generation

Returns:
```typescript
{
    operationId: string;
    status: "pending" | "completed" | "failed";
    progress?: string; // e.g., "45 seconds elapsed"
    path?: string; // If completed
    error?: string; // If failed
    prompt: string;
    model: string;
    startTime: string;
}
```

Implementation:
1. Look up operation in pendingOperations or check if already in videoHistory
2. If pending: call client.operations.get() to check current status
3. If completed: save video and update state
4. Return current status with metadata

Use case: User started generation with background=true and wants to check progress.

Animate a still image with motion.

Parameters:
- imagePath: string (required) - Path to source image
- prompt: string (required) - Description of desired motion
- duration: enum (optional) - 4 | 6 | 8 seconds
- model: enum (optional) - Model to use
- background: boolean (optional) - Return immediately

Implementation:
1. Validate imagePath exists and is PNG/JPEG/WebP (Gemini recommendation)
2. Read image as base64
3. Include image in API request along with prompt
4. Use same polling infrastructure as text-to-video
5. Save resulting video

From spec:
```typescript
// Read image as base64
const imageBuffer = await fs.readFile(imagePath);
const imageBase64 = imageBuffer.toString('base64');
const mimeType = getMimeType(imagePath); // image/jpeg, image/png, etc.

// Include in request
const operation = await client.models.generateVideos({
    model: model,
    prompt: prompt,
    image: {
        mimeType: mimeType,
        data: imageBase64
    },
    config: { ... }
});
```

Extend a previously generated Veo video.

Parameters:
- videoPath: string (required) - Path to Veo-generated video
- prompt: string (required) - Continuation description
- background: boolean (optional)

Constraints from spec:
- Can extend by 7 seconds per call
- Up to 20 extensions (~148 seconds total)
- ONLY works with Veo-generated videos

Implementation:
1. Validate videoPath exists
2. Look up video in session history to get metadata
3. Check extensionCount < 20
4. Call extension API
5. Update extensionCount in metadata
6. Save extended video (or replace original?)

```typescript
// Track extensions
const video = videoHistory.find(v => v.path === videoPath);
if (!video) {
    throw new Error("Can only extend Veo-generated videos from this session");
}
if (video.extensionCount >= 20) {
    throw new Error("Maximum 20 extensions reached (~148 seconds)");
}

// Call extension API
const operation = await client.models.extendVideo({
    video: videoPath,
    prompt: prompt
});

// Update metadata after success
video.extensionCount++;
```

Question: Does extension create new file or modify existing? Spec unclear.
